                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 14867/8.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Rives</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Vienna</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1909-09-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 30, 1909</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Rives says he has been requested by the minister for foreign affairs to ask
                    that the United States customs authorities accept certificates of chambers of
                    commerce of Austria-Hungary and extend to Austria-Hungary the same privileges,
                    as to Germany, until enforcement of Payne bill, and requests answer by
                    cable.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
